in this point of view.

00:42:42.950 --> 00:42:48.330 align:middle line:84%
And so the climate change
agenda has infected the left.

00:42:48.330 --> 00:42:50.350 align:middle line:84%
They're playing on
their want to do

00:42:50.350 --> 00:42:52.340 align:middle line:90%
something good for the planet.

00:42:52.340 --> 00:42:57.190 align:middle line:84%
So their actions are
predicated on ameliorating

00:42:57.190 --> 00:43:00.610 align:middle line:84%
their emotions about
what they're being told

00:43:00.610 --> 00:43:03.280 align:middle line:84%
is happening to the planet
and no more than that.

00:43:03.280 --> 00:43:06.050 align:middle line:84%
Because if rationally we
look at this, intelligently

00:43:06.050 --> 00:43:09.940 align:middle line:84%
we look at this, we look
at the science unbiasedly--

00:43:09.940 --> 00:43:11.780 align:middle line:84%
one of the
predications of science

00:43:11.780 --> 00:43:14.710 align:middle line:90%
is unbiased observation--

00:43:14.710 --> 00:43:17.230 align:middle line:84%
that we would come to
these other conclusions.

00:43:17.230 --> 00:43:19.210 align:middle line:84%
But we're thinking
with our emotions,

00:43:19.210 --> 00:43:21.610 align:middle line:84%
and it's corrupted
emotional thinking.

00:43:21.610 --> 00:43:24.010 align:middle line:84%
And that's ultimately
the problem--

00:43:24.010 --> 00:43:25.780 align:middle line:84%
is that we can't get
out of our emotions

00:43:25.780 --> 00:43:28.120 align:middle line:84%
to think about these
things that clouds

00:43:28.120 --> 00:43:31.580 align:middle line:90%
how we approach a problem.

00:43:31.580 --> 00:43:33.580 align:middle line:84%
And that's going
to be a downfall.

00:43:33.580 --> 00:43:37.450 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is it accurate to
say that this coming ice

00:43:37.450 --> 00:43:39.640 align:middle line:90%
age is starting now?

00:43:39.640 --> 00:43:42.350 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: I would say the sun
is signaling that very, very

00:43:42.350 --> 00:43:43.150 align:middle line:90%
strongly.

00:43:43.150 --> 00:43:43.690 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You would?

00:43:43.690 --> 00:43:44.140 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: I would.

00:43:44.140 --> 00:43:44.940 align:middle line:90%
I would.

00:43:44.940 --> 00:43:48.340 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How many meteorologists
and weather forecasters would

00:43:48.340 --> 00:43:50.800 align:middle line:90%
agree with you percentage-wise?

00:43:50.800 --> 00:43:52.040 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Single digits.

00:43:52.040 --> 00:43:52.840 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That low?

00:43:52.840 --> 00:43:53.910 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Oh, yeah.

00:43:53.910 --> 00:43:54.710 align:middle line:90%
Oh, yeah.

00:43:54.710 --> 00:43:56.140 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Though you
think you're right.

00:43:56.140 --> 00:43:56.973 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Oh, yeah.

00:43:56.973 --> 00:43:58.150 align:middle line:90%
Oh, yeah.

00:43:58.150 --> 00:44:00.330 align:middle line:84%
There's always the
first one that's right.

00:44:00.330 --> 00:44:02.090 align:middle line:84%
And the second one
is the one that's

00:44:02.090 --> 00:44:04.500 align:middle line:84%
able to convince others that
the first one is correct.

00:44:04.500 --> 00:44:06.500 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And what are the
telltale signs for us?

00:44:06.500 --> 00:44:12.230 align:middle line:84%
What will we see to back
up what you just said?

00:44:12.230 --> 00:44:13.344 align:middle line:90%
Longer winters?

00:44:13.344 --> 00:44:14.260 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Ultimately.

00:44:14.260 --> 00:44:16.670 align:middle line:84%
Ultimately, it would
be the longer winters.

00:44:16.670 --> 00:44:19.340 align:middle line:84%
Now, as long as we have
the contaminating effects

00:44:19.340 --> 00:44:21.950 align:middle line:84%
of geoengineering
in play, we're not

00:44:21.950 --> 00:44:24.800 align:middle line:84%
going to get a true read
on what's happening.

00:44:24.800 --> 00:44:29.320 align:middle line:84%
And that may be the reason
why it is happening--

00:44:29.320 --> 00:44:32.360 align:middle line:90%
is to delay this inevitable.

00:44:32.360 --> 00:44:34.310 align:middle line:84%
And that would be
worth them going

00:44:34.310 --> 00:44:38.510 align:middle line:84%
all in on the geoengineering,
chemtrail, climate change

00:44:38.510 --> 00:44:39.620 align:middle line:90%
program--

00:44:39.620 --> 00:44:44.240 align:middle line:90%
is to delay this inevitability.

00:44:44.240 --> 00:44:46.787 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are you hopeful
for our outcome here?

00:44:46.787 --> 00:44:47.870 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Oh, absolutely.

00:44:47.870 --> 00:44:48.410 align:middle line:90%
We're humans.

00:44:48.410 --> 00:44:48.950 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You are?

00:44:48.950 --> 00:44:50.090 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Oh, absolutely.

00:44:50.090 --> 00:44:51.770 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Because it seems
like doom and gloom.

00:44:51.770 --> 00:44:53.228 align:middle line:84%
So you're saying
there's hope here.

00:44:53.228 --> 00:44:55.970 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Oh, absolutely.

00:44:55.970 --> 00:45:01.840 align:middle line:84%
On the other side of this is
going to be a different truth,

00:45:01.840 --> 00:45:03.530 align:middle line:84%
so we can talk
about these things.

00:45:03.530 --> 00:45:06.320 align:middle line:84%
And a part of it-- and I don't
want to be revolutionary--

00:45:06.320 --> 00:45:08.490 align:middle line:90%
is a change in leadership--

00:45:08.490 --> 00:45:11.070 align:middle line:84%
a change in leadership so
we can have honest discourse

00:45:11.070 --> 00:45:14.310 align:middle line:84%
and discussion, not just in
this country, but planet wide.

00:45:14.310 --> 00:45:16.440 align:middle line:90%
We're all in this together.

00:45:16.440 --> 00:45:18.650 align:middle line:90%
And that is what excites me.

00:45:18.650 --> 00:45:22.200 align:middle line:90%
And I feel that that's close.

00:45:22.200 --> 00:45:26.070 align:middle line:84%
There is nothing that
happens it isn't ordained.

00:45:26.070 --> 00:45:27.780 align:middle line:90%
That's just how it is.

00:45:27.780 --> 00:45:29.910 align:middle line:84%
Things happen for a
reason, and so we just

00:45:29.910 --> 00:45:31.770 align:middle line:90%
have to let this play out.

00:45:31.770 --> 00:45:34.470 align:middle line:84%
There is something very,
very beautiful, George.

00:45:34.470 --> 00:45:37.420 align:middle line:84%
And it is not that
far off in the future.

00:45:37.420 --> 00:45:40.740 align:middle line:84%
And if we can just let go
of all this doom and gloom,

00:45:40.740 --> 00:45:42.510 align:middle line:90%
it's going to play itself out.

00:45:42.510 --> 00:45:45.650 align:middle line:84%
There isn't a single
birth that isn't painful

00:45:45.650 --> 00:45:47.227 align:middle line:90%
and a little bit bloody.

00:45:47.227 --> 00:45:49.560 align:middle line:84%
But then there are tears of
joy on the other side of it.

00:45:49.560 --> 00:45:51.310 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And is it the
bottom line, Scott,

00:45:51.310 --> 00:45:54.580 align:middle line:84%
that we are in cycles
on this planet?

00:45:54.580 --> 00:45:55.770 align:middle line:90%
It gets warmer.

00:45:55.770 --> 00:45:57.060 align:middle line:90%
It gets Colder.

00:45:57.060 --> 00:45:58.500 align:middle line:90%
It always did.

00:45:58.500 --> 00:45:59.470 align:middle line:90%
It always will.

00:45:59.470 --> 00:46:03.330 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: And if we can't
accommodate that variability,

00:46:03.330 --> 00:46:05.820 align:middle line:84%
then we need to
re-evaluate how we're

00:46:05.820 --> 00:46:08.520 align:middle line:84%
living in our relationship
with this planet.

00:46:08.520 --> 00:46:10.290 align:middle line:84%
It's the same with
living along the rivers

00:46:10.290 --> 00:46:11.790 align:middle line:90%
and along the coastlines.

00:46:11.790 --> 00:46:13.680 align:middle line:84%
They need to have
room to breathe.

00:46:13.680 --> 00:46:16.170 align:middle line:84%
It is not smart to build
up to the coastline.

00:46:16.170 --> 00:46:19.200 align:middle line:84%
It may look great, and
it's a great vacation spot,

00:46:19.200 --> 00:46:21.210 align:middle line:90%
but it's not very bright.

00:46:21.210 --> 00:46:25.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Knowing what you know,
where would you love to live?

00:46:25.830 --> 00:46:27.636 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Someplace warm.

00:46:27.636 --> 00:46:31.810 align:middle line:84%
And a move is coming in my
future, and it is to the south.

00:46:31.810 --> 00:46:32.610 align:middle line:90%
It is to the south.

00:46:32.610 --> 00:46:34.526 align:middle line:84%
Maybe we'll talk about
that on your radio show

00:46:34.526 --> 00:46:35.770 align:middle line:90%
in the near future.

00:46:35.770 --> 00:46:36.900 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Interesting take.

00:46:36.900 --> 00:46:37.700 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:46:37.700 --> 00:46:40.720 align:middle line:84%
So we've talked
about what is coming.

00:46:40.720 --> 00:46:42.810 align:middle line:90%
How do we react to that?

00:46:42.810 --> 00:46:45.060 align:middle line:90%
There could be wars over water.

00:46:45.060 --> 00:46:47.100 align:middle line:84%
What will happen to
our food supply that

00:46:47.100 --> 00:46:51.330 align:middle line:84%
relies so much on farming
if we have these colder

00:46:51.330 --> 00:46:54.330 align:middle line:90%
streaks and these icier times?

00:46:54.330 --> 00:46:55.480 align:middle line:90%
What are we going to do?

00:46:55.480 --> 00:46:56.938 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: We're
going to come back

00:46:56.938 --> 00:47:01.130 align:middle line:84%
to sourcing food from
inside of 200 miles.

00:47:01.130 --> 00:47:02.840 align:middle line:84%
That's just the way
it's going to be.

00:47:02.840 --> 00:47:03.990 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Out of necessity?

00:47:03.990 --> 00:47:05.156 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Out of necessity.

00:47:05.156 --> 00:47:10.590 align:middle line:84%
We will be forced to comply
with the way it used to be.

00:47:10.590 --> 00:47:13.980 align:middle line:84%
This whole shipping apples
from China to the States

00:47:13.980 --> 00:47:15.900 align:middle line:84%
because the Washington
farmers don't

00:47:15.900 --> 00:47:19.830 align:middle line:84%
do something right
or grapes from Chile

00:47:19.830 --> 00:47:22.890 align:middle line:84%
in the middle of
winter is idiotic.

00:47:22.890 --> 00:47:23.937 align:middle line:90%
It's nice to have.

00:47:23.937 --> 00:47:24.770 align:middle line:90%
It's great to have--

00:47:24.770 --> 00:47:26.460 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Or contaminated
Romaine lettuce,

00:47:26.460 --> 00:47:28.060 align:middle line:84%
and that's happening
all over the place.

00:47:28.060 --> 00:47:28.860 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: It is.

00:47:28.860 --> 00:47:32.130 align:middle line:84%
But it sets us up for
spectacular failures,

00:47:32.130 --> 00:47:35.800 align:middle line:84%
because we have this incredibly
centralized food distribution

00:47:35.800 --> 00:47:36.600 align:middle line:90%
system.

00:47:36.600 --> 00:47:39.900 align:middle line:84%
And this centralization
is two things--

00:47:39.900 --> 00:47:42.840 align:middle line:90%
ports and petroleum.

00:47:42.840 --> 00:47:45.030 align:middle line:84%
You take out one
of those things,

00:47:45.030 --> 00:47:46.510 align:middle line:90%
and we can't feed ourselves.

00:47:46.510 --> 00:47:48.440 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, if the
rivers all freeze up,

00:47:48.440 --> 00:47:48.690 align:middle line:90%
what are we going to do?

00:47:48.690 --> 00:47:50.981 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: If the rivers
freeze, or if we have tsunamis

00:47:50.981 --> 00:47:52.740 align:middle line:84%
in the Pacific, or
we have breakdowns

00:47:52.740 --> 00:47:54.870 align:middle line:84%
in pipeline of
petroleum distribution,

00:47:54.870 --> 00:47:57.910 align:middle line:90%
there is no backup.

00:47:57.910 --> 00:48:00.150 align:middle line:84%
There is no backup for
tankers, for shippers,

00:48:00.150 --> 00:48:01.950 align:middle line:90%
for these big ships.

00:48:01.950 --> 00:48:02.850 align:middle line:90%
There's no backup.

00:48:02.850 --> 00:48:04.891 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is this going to
change the way we live?

00:48:04.891 --> 00:48:06.990 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: Absolutely,
and it's supposed to.

00:48:06.990 --> 00:48:08.640 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Probably
already is, isn't it?

00:48:08.640 --> 00:48:09.848 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Slowly and surely.

00:48:09.848 --> 00:48:12.270 align:middle line:84%
And there are people
out there more conscious

00:48:12.270 --> 00:48:15.030 align:middle line:84%
than others who are
leading this change

00:48:15.030 --> 00:48:17.910 align:middle line:84%
neighborhood by neighborhood,
community by community.

00:48:17.910 --> 00:48:18.870 align:middle line:90%
And it's happening.

00:48:18.870 --> 00:48:23.980 align:middle line:84%
So in many ways, those foot
soldiers are already at work.

00:48:23.980 --> 00:48:27.060 align:middle line:84%
They're doing their job
as they're supposed to do.

00:48:27.060 --> 00:48:31.000 align:middle line:84%
Like me coming out and talking
about this topic 15 years ago,

00:48:31.000 --> 00:48:36.360 align:middle line:84%
they are creating these small
farm-to-table communities.

00:48:36.360 --> 00:48:38.550 align:middle line:84%
And it's important
that they do the work

00:48:38.550 --> 00:48:40.710 align:middle line:90%
that they're called to do.

00:48:40.710 --> 00:48:43.080 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are we going
to find ourselves

00:48:43.080 --> 00:48:45.780 align:middle line:84%
with shorter summers,
longer winters?

00:48:45.780 --> 00:48:48.750 align:middle line:90%


00:48:48.750 --> 00:48:50.280 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: I think, yes.

00:48:50.280 --> 00:48:52.440 align:middle line:84%
But the bigger
thing will probably

00:48:52.440 --> 00:48:55.410 align:middle line:90%
be that it's simply drier.

00:48:55.410 --> 00:48:58.712 align:middle line:84%
As the climate cools,
it will be drier.

00:48:58.712 --> 00:48:59.670 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: More droughts?

00:48:59.670 --> 00:49:01.890 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: More droughts.

00:49:01.890 --> 00:49:03.940 align:middle line:84%
Kansas is covered
with prairie now.

00:49:03.940 --> 00:49:05.739 align:middle line:90%
It may not be so green.

00:49:05.739 --> 00:49:06.780 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's shocking.

00:49:06.780 --> 00:49:09.321 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: It's only going green
because we're pumping water.

00:49:09.321 --> 00:49:11.032 align:middle line:84%
And we've nearly
extinguished a lot of--

00:49:11.032 --> 00:49:12.990 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We've got a lot
of rain in the Midwest

00:49:12.990 --> 00:49:14.270 align:middle line:84%
this year, but
that could change.

00:49:14.270 --> 00:49:15.394 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: It could change.

00:49:15.394 --> 00:49:17.250 align:middle line:84%
But I think drier
will be the key word.

00:49:17.250 --> 00:49:19.800 align:middle line:90%
And that's why the greenhouses--

00:49:19.800 --> 00:49:23.850 align:middle line:84%
to contain the evaporation
and to recycle and become--

00:49:23.850 --> 00:49:27.570 align:middle line:84%
we've become units, units,
units, units, units.

00:49:27.570 --> 00:49:29.670 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You know, we
look at some movies.

00:49:29.670 --> 00:49:32.550 align:middle line:84%
I remember one with
Jeff Goldblum who

00:49:32.550 --> 00:49:35.190 align:middle line:90%
was predicting certain things.

00:49:35.190 --> 00:49:38.460 align:middle line:84%
And he would tell
people in Washington,

00:49:38.460 --> 00:49:40.380 align:middle line:90%
and nobody would listen to him.

00:49:40.380 --> 00:49:44.850 align:middle line:84%
Do we have that kind of rapport
right now in Washington where

00:49:44.850 --> 00:49:48.780 align:middle line:84%
you've got some meteorologists
and climatologists saying,

00:49:48.780 --> 00:49:50.310 align:middle line:84%
you've got to get
ready for this.

00:49:50.310 --> 00:49:52.060 align:middle line:90%
There's a ice age coming.

00:49:52.060 --> 00:49:54.840 align:middle line:84%
We're not prepared,
and nobody listens?

00:49:54.840 --> 00:49:56.070 align:middle line:90%
Or do they listen?

00:49:56.070 --> 00:49:59.190 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: I think they
listen, but there is an agenda.

00:49:59.190 --> 00:50:04.530 align:middle line:84%
And more importantly, there's
an event separating that reality

00:50:04.530 --> 00:50:06.110 align:middle line:90%
from right now.

00:50:06.110 --> 00:50:08.560 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know
whether it's war,

00:50:08.560 --> 00:50:11.550 align:middle line:84%
whether it's magnetic
field change, whether it's

00:50:11.550 --> 00:50:16.620 align:middle line:84%
a hit from the sun, whether
it's a volcanic eruption that

00:50:16.620 --> 00:50:20.210 align:middle line:84%
clouds the planet and
precipitates this ice age.

00:50:20.210 --> 00:50:22.710 align:middle line:84%
It could be a combination
of all of those.

00:50:22.710 --> 00:50:25.660 align:middle line:10%
But there will be an
awakening of humanity.

00:50:25.660 --> 00:50:28.230 align:middle line:10%
And it will be that
awakening and that bestowal

00:50:28.230 --> 00:50:30.780 align:middle line:10%
of consciousness
that will allow us

00:50:30.780 --> 00:50:35.190 align:middle line:10%
the awareness to navigate these
issues in these coming times.

00:50:35.190 --> 00:50:38.310 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: If you were speaking
before a group of scientists

00:50:38.310 --> 00:50:39.300 align:middle line:90%
right now--

00:50:39.300 --> 00:50:42.450 align:middle line:84%
climatologists-- what
would you be telling them?

00:50:42.450 --> 00:50:45.500 align:middle line:90%


00:50:45.500 --> 00:50:48.290 align:middle line:84%
Doesn't matter whether
they believe you or not.

00:50:48.290 --> 00:50:49.970 align:middle line:84%
But what would you
be telling them?

00:50:49.970 --> 00:50:51.800 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Enjoy today.

00:50:51.800 --> 00:50:53.510 align:middle line:90%
Enjoy today.

00:50:53.510 --> 00:50:57.992 align:middle line:10%
Live for now and
put aside what--

00:50:57.992 --> 00:51:00.025 align:middle line:10%
in science, there is this rite--

00:51:00.025 --> 00:51:02.240 align:middle line:10%
R-I-T-E-- of being right--

00:51:02.240 --> 00:51:06.590 align:middle line:10%
R-I-G-H-T. There's this
rite of being right.

00:51:06.590 --> 00:51:11.840 align:middle line:84%
And don't offend me and take
away my rite of being right.

00:51:11.840 --> 00:51:13.280 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Old Boy Scout line--

00:51:13.280 --> 00:51:14.960 align:middle line:90%
be prepared.

00:51:14.960 --> 00:51:16.740 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we
should be doing.

00:51:16.740 --> 00:51:20.900 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: And each one has a
different place in all of this.

00:51:20.900 --> 00:51:24.020 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: If you were somebody
living in the northern area

00:51:24.020 --> 00:51:26.390 align:middle line:84%
of the United States,
would you move and try

00:51:26.390 --> 00:51:29.630 align:middle line:90%
to go down to Florida or Texas?

00:51:29.630 --> 00:51:31.690 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: I don't know
if that's far enough.

00:51:31.690 --> 00:51:32.490 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:51:32.490 --> 00:51:34.350 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: And I'll
leave it at that.

00:51:34.350 --> 00:51:35.270 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if
that's far enough.

00:51:35.270 --> 00:51:36.603 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What a way to leave it.

